org.apache.beam.sdk.metrics

Class DistributionCell

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.beam.sdk.metrics.DistributionCell
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Distribution, Metric, MetricCell<Distribution,DistributionData>

    @Experimental(value=METRICS)
public class DistributionCell
extends Object
implements MetricCell<Distribution,DistributionData>, Distribution
    Tracks the current value (and delta) for a Distribution metric.

    This class generally shouldn't be used directly. The only exception is within a runner where a distribution is being reported for a specific step (rather than the distribution in the current context). In that case retrieving the underlying cell and reporting directly to it avoids a step of indirection.
